    <section>
            <div class="text-center mb-16">
                <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">How to Use – Quick User Guide</h2>
                <p class="max-w-2xl mx-auto text-gray-600">Professional and clear User Guide section with three structured paragraphs</p>
            </div>
    <div class="cards">
        <div class="card" data-index="0">
            <div class="card__inner">
                <div class="card__image-container">
                    <img class="card__image"
                             src="https://media.istockphoto.com/id/1303694212/vector/online-customer-service-concept-operator-of-call-center-office-consulting-a-client.jpg?s=612x612&w=0&k=20&c=CgL9kAn_BX7rXh2L4Nqq0ath7IqS0LI7BqTVpPbS1nE="
                         alt="" />
                </div>
                <div class="card__content">
                    <h1 class="card__title">For End Users</h1>
                    <p class="card__description">
                            As an end user, once you log in, your main goal is to submit facility-related complaints such as broken lights, internet issues, or AC faults. Simply go to the "New Request" section, fill in your issue details, select the appropriate facility (e.g., IT Lab, Auditorium), and submit. You can then visit the "Track Requests" page to monitor the real-time progress of your complaint — from Pending to Assigned, In Progress, and finally Closed. You’ll also see who’s working on it and when it was last updated.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card" data-index="0">
            <div class="card__inner">
                <div class="card__image-container">
                    <img class="card__image"
                             src="https://t4.ftcdn.net/jpg/04/19/31/45/360_F_419314575_XVvF5CuDgWGjUl7Pzs2dfWnzj9SNsKJG.jpg"
                         alt="" />
                </div>
                <div class="card__content">
                    <h1 class="card__title">For Facility Heads</h1>
                    <p class="card__description">
                            Facility Heads are responsible for overseeing all complaints submitted under their assigned facilities. Upon logging in, they can access the "Assign Requests" page, which lists pending complaints. They can then review the details and assign them to appropriate Assignees. The dashboard displays stats like total assigned, pending, and resolved requests. Facility Heads also have visibility into request statuses across all categories (not just pending), giving them full control to ensure timely resolution and team accountability.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card" data-index="0">
            <div class="card__inner">
                <div class="card__image-container">
                    <img class="card__image"
                             src="https://img.freepik.com/free-vector/technical-support-concept-idea-customer-service-consultant-support-clients-help-them-with-problems-providing-customer-with-valuable-information-vector-illustration-cartoon-style_613284-2779.jpg?semt=ais_hybrid&w=740"
                         alt="" />
                </div>
                <div class="card__content">
                        <h1 class="card__title">For Assignees</h1>
                    <p class="card__description">
                            Assignees are the technical personnel who resolve complaints. Once logged in, Assignees are shown their total assigned tasks, including those pending, in progress, or completed. From the "My Tasks" section, they can view detailed descriptions of each request and update the task status accordingly — for example, from "Assigned" to "In Progress" and finally to "Closed" once resolved. This ensures clear communication between all parties and keeps the help desk workflow efficient and transparent.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    </section>

    <!-- FAQ Section -->
    <section id="faq" class="py-16 bg-white">
        <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
            <div class="text-center mb-16">
                <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
                <p class="max-w-2xl mx-auto text-gray-600">Find answers to common questions about the OHD System</p>
            </div>

            <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
                <div class="accordion-group space-y-4">
                    <!-- Question 1 -->
                    <div class="accordion border rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
                        <button class="accordion-btn w-full flex justify-between items-center p-6 focus:outline-none bg-gray-50">
                            <span class="text-lg font-medium text-left">Q1: What is the Online Help Desk (OHD) system?</span>
                            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-6 w-6 text-indigo-600 transition-transform duration-300" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
                            </svg>
                        </button>
                        <div class="accordion-content px-6 pb-6">
                            <p class="text-gray-600">The OHD is a centralized platform where users can submit, track, and manage facility-related complaints or requests (e.g., maintenance, IT support, repairs). The system streamlines communication between users, facility heads, and assignees.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Question 2 -->
                    <div class="accordion border rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
                        <button class="accordion-btn w-full flex justify-between items-center p-6 focus:outline-none bg-gray-50">
                            <span class="text-lg font-medium text-left"> Q2: Who can use the system and what are the roles?</span>
                            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-6 w-6 text-indigo-600 transition-transform duration-300" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
                            </svg>
                        </button>
                        <div class="accordion-content px-6 pb-6">
                            <p class="text-gray-600">
                                Admin: Manages users, facilities, and approvals.<br>
                                End User: Submits and tracks help desk requests.<br>
                                Facility Head: Reviews and assigns requests to assignees.<br>
                                Assignee: Resolves assigned tasks and updates their statuses.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Question 3 -->
                    <div class="accordion border rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
                        <button class="accordion-btn w-full flex justify-between items-center p-6 focus:outline-none bg-gray-50">
                            <span class="text-lg font-medium text-left"> Q3: How do I submit a new request?</span>
                            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-6 w-6 text-indigo-600 transition-transform duration-300" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
                            </svg>
                        </button>
                        <div class="accordion-content px-6 pb-6">
                            <p class="text-gray-600">After logging in as a User, navigate to the “New Request” page, fill in the issue title and description, select your facility, and click Submit.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Question 4 -->
                    <div class="accordion border rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
                        <button class="accordion-btn w-full flex justify-between items-center p-6 focus:outline-none bg-gray-50">
                            <span class="text-lg font-medium text-left"> Q4: How can I check the status of my submitted request?</span>
                            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-6 w-6 text-indigo-600 transition-transform duration-300" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
                            </svg>
                        </button>
                        <div class="accordion-content px-6 pb-6">
                            <p class="text-gray-600">Go to “Track Requests”. You will see all your recent submissions along with their statuses: Pending, Assigned, In Progress, Closed.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Question 5 -->
                    <div class="accordion border rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
                        <button class="accordion-btn w-full flex justify-between items-center p-6 focus:outline-none bg-gray-50">
                            <span class="text-lg font-medium text-left"> Q5: What happens after I submit a request?</span>
                            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-6 w-6 text-indigo-600 transition-transform duration-300" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
                            </svg>
                        </button>
                        <div class="accordion-content px-6 pb-6">
                            <p class="text-gray-600">The Facility Head of your selected facility will review your request and assign it to an appropriate Assignee. The Assignee will then work on resolving the issue and updating its progress.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Question 6 -->
                    <div class="accordion border rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
                        <button class="accordion-btn w-full flex justify-between items-center p-6 focus:outline-none bg-gray-50">
                            <span class="text-lg font-medium text-left"> Q6: Can I cancel or delete a submitted request?</span>
                            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-6 w-6 text-indigo-600 transition-transform duration-300" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
                            </svg>
                        </button>
                        <div class="accordion-content px-6 pb-6">
                            <p class="text-gray-600">No, users cannot delete requests. However, they can track them. If a mistake is made, contact the Admin to request changes.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Question 7 -->
                    <div class="accordion border rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
                        <button class="accordion-btn w-full flex justify-between items-center p-6 focus:outline-none bg-gray-50">
                            <span class="text-lg font-medium text-left"> Q7: How do I update my profile or change password?</span>
                            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-6 w-6 text-indigo-600 transition-transform duration-300" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
                            </svg>
                        </button>
                        <div class="accordion-content px-6 pb-6">
                            <p class="text-gray-600">Click on “Profile” in the side navigation. You can edit your name, username, email, and also change your password securely.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Question 8 -->
                    <div class="accordion border rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
                        <button class="accordion-btn w-full flex justify-between items-center p-6 focus:outline-none bg-gray-50">
                            <span class="text-lg font-medium text-left"> Q8: I forgot my password. What should I do?</span>
                            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-6 w-6 text-indigo-600 transition-transform duration-300" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
                            </svg>
                        </button>
                        <div class="accordion-content px-6 pb-6">
                            <p class="text-gray-600">There is currently no “Forgot Password” feature. Please contact the Admin for manual reset or login recovery.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Question 9 -->
                    <div class="accordion border rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
                        <button class="accordion-btn w-full flex justify-between items-center p-6 focus:outline-none bg-gray-50">
                            <span class="text-lg font-medium text-left"> Q9: How are requests prioritized?</span>
                            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-6 w-6 text-indigo-600 transition-transform duration-300" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
                            </svg>
                        </button>
                        <div class="accordion-content px-6 pb-6">
                            <p class="text-gray-600">Requests are assigned based on the availability of assignees and urgency. The Facility Head oversees proper routing and may adjust priorities.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Question 10 -->
                    <div class="accordion border rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
                        <button class="accordion-btn w-full flex justify-between items-center p-6 focus:outline-none bg-gray-50">
                            <span class="text-lg font-medium text-left"> Q10: How do I know when my issue is resolved?</span>
                            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-6 w-6 text-indigo-600 transition-transform duration-300" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
                            </svg>
                        </button>
                        <div class="accordion-content px-6 pb-6">
                            <p class="text-gray-600">Once an assignee marks the task as Resolved, it will reflect in your tracking dashboard. You’ll also be able to see who resolved it and when.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Question 11 -->
                    <div class="accordion border rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
                        <button class="accordion-btn w-full flex justify-between items-center p-6 focus:outline-none bg-gray-50">
                            <span class="text-lg font-medium text-left"> Q11: How do Facility Heads manage requests?</span>
                            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-6 w-6 text-indigo-600 transition-transform duration-300" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
                            </svg>
                        </button>
                        <div class="accordion-content px-6 pb-6">
                            <p class="text-gray-600">Facility Heads can view all submitted requests under their facility (regardless of status), assign them to assignees, and monitor progress.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Question 12 -->
                    <div class="accordion border rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
                        <button class="accordion-btn w-full flex justify-between items-center p-6 focus:outline-none bg-gray-50">
                            <span class="text-lg font-medium text-left"> Q12: What types of issues should be reported?</span>
                            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-6 w-6 text-indigo-600 transition-transform duration-300" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
                            </svg>
                        </button>
                        <div class="accordion-content px-6 pb-6">
                            <p class="text-gray-600">Any facility-related problems like broken equipment, network issues, IT malfunctions, power failures, cleaning complaints, etc., can be reported.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Question 13 -->
                    <div class="accordion border rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
                        <button class="accordion-btn w-full flex justify-between items-center p-6 focus:outline-none bg-gray-50">
                            <span class="text-lg font-medium text-left"> Q13: Is there a history of resolved issues?</span>
                            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-6 w-6 text-indigo-600 transition-transform duration-300" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
                            </svg>
                        </button>
                        <div class="accordion-content px-6 pb-6">
                            <p class="text-gray-600">Yes. Users, Facility Heads, and Assignees can all access records of past requests, their statuses, assigned personnel, and timestamps.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Question 14 -->
                    <div class="accordion border rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
                        <button class="accordion-btn w-full flex justify-between items-center p-6 focus:outline-none bg-gray-50">
                            <span class="text-lg font-medium text-left"> Q14: How secure is my data?</span>
                            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-6 w-6 text-indigo-600 transition-transform duration-300" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
                            </svg>
                        </button>
                        <div class="accordion-content px-6 pb-6">
                            <p class="text-gray-600">Each user logs in with credentials. Only assigned roles can access their allowed actions. Sensitive actions like password change or assignments are protected.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Question 15 -->
